content: Very helpful for understanding caffeine intake and effect.
How does it track caffeine metabolism. Based on weight and caffeine bf half life? Is there an option for if you're a slow metabolizerkf caffeine (genetic testing)

Pretty good. A little buggy, but useful and basic function is there. Only thing I'm missing is that I can't scroll ahead to the future and plan out doses. I can add future-dated entries, but the graph stops too soon and won't let me scroll. Unfortunately, this prevents me from targeting a certain caffeine level at bedtime.
replyContent: Appreciate the feedback and glad you are finding utility in the app. We will consider expanding the future projection in an up coming release. Great suggestion. If you have more detail on the buggy things you mention please share at rogan.software@gmail.com.

content: Clearing my cache and data solved the problem. Thanks. I'm still sad about loosing all my history and the hassle of generating my drinks all over again (it's not the first time this happens). Please make it possible to auto-backup (history and presets) and to import old data (without clearing the current data - append).
replyContent: Sorry you are having trouble with the recent update. Your database seems to be corrupt. You will need to clear storage for the app in settings. Settings -> Apps & notifications -> Caffeine Tracker -> Storage and cache -> Clear storage. Feel free to reach out by email if you need more help: rogan.softare@gmail.com

content: Great app for monitoring caffeine intake and half life. The ability to give the time period of a drink consumed would be great though. For example, drinking an energy drink over the course of an hour or two vs entering the entire thing all at one time as it currently is. Splitting it into several entries would accomplish this but if the app could spread it out and do the math for me that would be great
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback! Latest release (1.4.8) allows a custom ramp up period per intake.

content: Great app and thanks for your feedback. I added a caffeine tablet in which worked well. I've gone from 500mg caffeine a day to zero in nine days, quite painlessly apart from headache yesterday which I managed with disprin. Managed any threatening onset of headaches by timing caffeine intake which stopped headaches but allowed me to keep reducing slowly. Feel fantastic. Thank you.
replyContent: So glad to hear this! Thanks for sharing.

content: Does the job well. UI is kind of simple but it works.
Waste of money
Didnt calculate drinks correctly. Asked for refund.

This app is almost everything I need! A little more customization would be nice--it would be cool to offer yerba mate, guyasa, other teas--but I don't mind doing the math in my head. Honestly, this app changed my life. Cut my caffeine intake in half.
replyContent: Glad you're enjoying the app! You can add in your own custom beverages (app bar -> 3 dot overflow menu -> Manage drinks).

content: I think its great for coffee lovers....for five stars add an "energy drink" oz counter, thanks!

I have updated my review to 4 stars due to improvements made to the app. Unfortunately the latest update made the app excruciatingly slow due to the drink database and I had to clear it and start over, having to add the custom drinks back in.
This is the only app that does exactly what I want. Thank you
Easy to use and can customise with your own drinks.
One of my absolute favorites! Thank you so very much for the more useful graphs. I follow my caffeine so that I will be a hundred or below in time for bed, and you've made it much easier. Kudos!
Total waste of time. Confusing to use, just wanted to see how much I was consuming in a day. Hardly any drink options. Don't waste your money

Still working great. I quit caffeine but am now back to having it. The updates with the new graph are really nice, and the filter is handy. The export data feature is especially nice. One favor to ask - could you add an export/import for the drinks database? I've spent a lot of time adding drinks and sorting them, and if I ever have to reinstall the app or get a new phone, I would have to re-enter everything one at at time. I have been using this app for 4 years and it has been rock solid. Thank you.

Not a bad app, but could do with more detail on the times and mg of caffeine on the graph. Hard to tell what time I'm at what mg. Add more detail and the ability to zoom in on the graph and it's 5 stars. Edit: can now zoom in closer on graph, and see caffeine levels at specific times. A little buggy, but otherwise it's great. Changed from 3 to 4 stars!
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback! Working on an update to the graphing for next release. Looking forward to earning your 4th and 5th star! ðŸ˜‰ UPDATE: Version 1.4.7 released with chart updates.

content: Basic, but good caffeine tracker. Does what it does without annoying ads or unnecessarily complicated features. GUI could do with a bit of a redesign. A tabed interface with a button for the main screen, projection screen and intace screen would make the app a little easier to navigate.
It seems accurate. Saw some weird stuff going on with the clock when you enter the time of your caffeine intake. Other than that good
Well made app and easy to use

I use this every day to estimate and track caffeine levels at midnight to determine impact on sleep. The app works well, though it could be better. For instance, it would be helpful to be able to click on a bar for total daily caffeine consumption and see what you were at. Same thing with the metabolism curve - i'm really just guessing. I'd like to be able to slide the time to find the estimated caffeine amount rather than guessing. I'm also curious about the metabolism equation. Thank you!
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback! An update to the charts is coming soon. UPDATE: Version 1.4.7 released with improved charts.

content: The app crashes often and the caffeine it's "tracking" gets stuck on a number for days. I'd like refund if possible
I've noticed that the pie charts showing what's green red or blue are not exactly accurate. Hope this is fixed. Otherwise I really do like the app a lot.
Very good, no frills data tracker from thirty thousand feet. I think the best benefit is Behavioral modification.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback! Let us know what we can do to earn a 5th star.ðŸ˜‰

content: Can't look at history, or zoom in/ manipulate graph of caffeine projections

This app is quite good at monitoring the amount of caffeine in your system, however it has a few areas which are annoying / can be improved. It would be great if there was an option to add decaf tea and coffee (as they still contain caffeine). Also, the graph is good but would be useful to be able to slide it along and see beyond just a few hours ahead or behind.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback! You can add custom drinks as requested through overflow menu (app bar -> 3 dot -> manage drinks).

content: Pretty useful. Easy to use and it's been insightful to track my caffeine usage. It's hard to be too accurate as gauging how much caffeine you're consuming has a massive margin of error. Having different absorption rates though for tea vs coffee would be useful.
Nice concept, but what about black and green tea? Its caffeine has a much longer half-life and there is no way to reflect this in the app.
simple and useful

Great tool, it has allowed me to keep my caffeine levels at optimal levels throughout the day and have low enough levels to sleep well at night. I just take four caffeine pills throughout the day and only drink non caffeinated drinks now.
great app for tracking caffeine
works great.
only tracks last 24 hours

only app I've actually paid for in like five years (remember when we actually had to pay for most apps?) but worth a dollar, does exactly what I want. Shows current and future caffiene level, editable metabolism, can make custom drinks, can edit past/future. would like it if the graph could zoom (really hard to get an accurate estimate at a specific time in the future), but everything else works great
The app is light and simple and the calculations right.
This is pretty cool! Also the developer is very engaged in added requested features. Very happy!
replyContent: Glad you like the app and thanks for the feedback! Just released version 1.4.6 which allows input of future intakes. Hopefully earns us the 5th star in rating. :)

content: Really great app that shows general caffeine in bloodstream. Would be great if you could add half-life modifications/metabolosim modifications for those who differ from norm. The export function could also contain the decay data too. But, it is still a really great app!
Love that you can add the caffeine sources I use! Also super fast response from the devs!
replyContent: You can add custom sources in the drink management section. Overflow menu (3 dots in top menu) -> Manage drinks. Sorry for the inconvenience!

content: No option to input mg? I don't consume my caffeine through beverages and did not see an option to input direct mgs of caffeine.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback. A workaround might be to add a custom drink for your intake - with mg / oz value of 1. You would then be entering a mg quantity for ozs. Not ideal but functional. A fix will go on list for future release.

content: Definitely worth the dollar, and close to 5 stars. As noted by another review, having a decimal option for the entries would be great. Being able to enter a pure mg value (without an associated preset) would be nice as well.
Excellent caffeine tracker. The metabolism line graph could be improved by having hourly or three-hour verticals to help me better relate amount to time of day, but the app works well anyway.

Great app. Only improvements I can think of would be to allow for a decimal point, as there's a significant difference between 2 oz of espresso and 2.5, for example. It also would be helpful if it allowed for other measurements than just ounces. Lastly, I would like the option to record decaf coffee, as it does tend to include small amounts of caffeine that would be worth tracking. If there's ever an update, I'd love to have these suggestions taken into consideration! All in all, a great app though.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback! Most of what you ask for is already available. Under "settings", you can select from among several drink units options (oz, ml, cl, shots). Under "manage drinks" you can add and use your own custom "decaf coffee" drink too. We'll consider the decimal fraction drink units input for a future update. Thanks again.

content: Simple, does the job.
Well it works. But it's hideous. Ultra rudimentary/utilitarian.
Fairly user friendly. Does not hang
It's simple, and helpful!
Tried a few of the free caffeine tracker apps before giving this one a shot. Would have gone for this sooner if I knew how good it was.

A great app that actually uses a proper model of caffeine metabolism. However, there is limited numerical precision and roundinig issues, and no manual control of half-life for those that deviate from the mean value.
Well worth the dollar

Awesome!!! Lifesaver. Monitors how much caffeine is in your bloodstream. 
Perfect for keeping track of your energy level based on your caffeine 
intake. Easy to use. Programmer paid detailed attention on how to make your 
entries fast and easy.
Wish the graph went back more than 24 hours
Good not great, would be nice to see the levels a day or two further back
Good tracker but it needs to zero out drinks faster and the graph needs to be scalable OR it needs to more clearly predict when you'll reach a desired caffeine level.
Great app. Would like to be able to zoom in and out on graph to see it over several days rather than 24hrs.
Great basic app. Scalable graphs would be great.

The tracking is great, the charts are great, it does everything I like.  But it's only getting 3 stars from me because it constantly shows 1mg, 5mg, et cetera from any drinks I had up to the past 2 to 4 days. So it skews the numbers because it's not properly zeroing out caffeine intake in a proper amount of time.
For a while, the size of the labels on the graphs was too small. That was my only complaint. Now that's fixed. It's worth paying for the full version. They have put together a good reliable app.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback!

content: It's basic but does the job. The design of graphs is quite poor though
I've been using this for quite a while to monitor my caffeine levels seeing this is the only app I could find that would estimate the caffeine in my bloodstream. Always room for improvements.
As a fitness professional, I very much approve and appreciate this product. It helps me keep track of my caffeine intake, as well as clients that download it.
Great app, makes it easy to track how much caffeine you're consuming.
It works. Simple to use.

Fantastic app. What it does that the others don't - and what makes it worth the price - is that it shows you how long the caffeine you drink now will be in your body. Setting how much of my morning coffee was still affecting me at midnight or 4am was a real eye-opener. Also I saw that I didn't need as much as I thought because a lot is still active in the afternoon. I dramatically cut back my caffeine in just two weeks with this app. Highly recommended.
Some pie chart issues, but mostly ok
Simple to use, and gives me a good idea of my consumption so I don't go overboard. Great app.
Needs more caffeinated beverages tracked, and different volume units.

Overall the app is fantastic. I love that you can customize your drinks, that you can set your own personal goals, and that it helps you predict caffeine levels after so long. My only issue is I want to try to export the data and, no matter where I export the data to, it won't work because the data file is empty. Perfect 5 if I can get help on that.
replyContent: Fixed in version 1.4.3 released today!

content: Needs progressive intake, cuz no one drinks the whole cup of coffee in one instant.
Really like this app, especially the graphical presentation of the caffeine level. Would be even better with more accurate figures of how much is in each drink. Overall excellent app
Simple and stops me from too much caffeine daily

Would be nice to have more caffeine reference in the app instead of searching online. Would be nice to have more detailed history of levels over long time.  Would be nice to be able to remove drink from consumed list. update. Please, fix the editing bug. When I open the edit screen for drinks, then I'm not able to scroll through the whole list of drinks. I also not able to delete irrelevant drinks like Pepsi or Coca cola
Works as advertised
Nice and simple, gets the job done. Good stuff.
UI could be better. I'd like to see it more like AlcoDroid's. Pie chart colors are a little confusing.
Does what it should
Works great!
Does what it should. More presets would be nice. Great new design =]
Show when does effect wear off
It needs work
Helpful in seeing my caffine intake. Wish I could see several days at once not just last 24 hours

I like the fact that this app keeps everything very simple, but i was still expecting some functionalities to be better implemented since it is a paid app. - The coffee databases is too basic, i was expecting the complete list of "famous" coffee brands and products. - You can add your customized coffee, but they won't be included in the export file if you want save them before a mobile clean-up!!! - You can export data, but you can't import anything. I didn't try yet, but i doubt the data is automatically store on some cloud service. - Once you add a drink, you can't modify the history anymore in case you've done some mistake. Hope some improvement in the future will make me add some more stars to this app.

Love it!!!  Simple, direct, easy to use.  Had it for a few days and it already seems to be helping me sleep better at night, it makes it very easy to see when you've gone overboard with the caffeine and should slow it down.  There are other free caffeine tracker apps out there, but they are not as good, you get what you pay for.  As a person who loves coffee, sleeping, and keeping track of things with little graphs and charts LOL, this app is perfect for me!!!
Works well

I have definitely adjusted my habits after using this app.  I try to get get more of my drinking done in the morning. The graphs are my favorite part, but I would appreciate the ability to zoom in, or have an annotated cursor so I could get a precise prediction of my caffeine level at bedtime.  That would take this review to 5 stars.
It should take into account smoking as well since nicotine significantly speeds up caffeine metabolism
I'm able to monitor my caffeine intake and it will let me know when I've gone over.
Great
The dev needs to explain why the app needs permissions to access photos.
replyContent: Oh no!  Sorry you are disappointed with the app.  The app asks for permission to read/write to external storage not to access photos but to enable the export/import data feature.

content: Really good, you can add your own drinks too eg hot chocolate. I use this daily, helps me to easily see when I need to lay off the coffee/tea. Surprising easy to go over the recommended 400mg a day! This app has been invaluable in teaching me more about caffeine. I love it!

Suggestion: a planner for when you should have a coffee to time the caffein peak (eg. a test you have to take) or a low caffein level (for those who find it difficult to sleep with too much caffein in the system, a notification like "stop drinking coffee now to sleep better").

Not the prettiest app, and a little clunky in spots but overall great app for what you need it to do. I love the export feature and its fairly easy to open, enter data, and close after each coffee. I also like the choice of a pie chart as a quick representation of your levels.

Does what it says... mostly. I find it very useful but have a few suggestions. After a certain low point your liver eliminates the remaining caffeine much faster. It would be nice to account for that. Second, please allow "future" times, this lets people see "OK, what will be the consequence if I drink this now..."  It would be super useful to have an app like this that could track other things as well...
This app gives me the exact information I want, in an easy-to-use format, and I can customise the inputs. What more could you ask for?
I love the way it tells me ahead of time when I'll need to top up on coffee â˜º
Brilliant App, helps to max performance and improve sleep! One suggestion, amend the bottom axis on the graph to 4 hour intervals and include vertical grid lines so it is easier to read.

Nice features, would be great if the user could scroll back the caffeine level history chart for a week or so rather than just showing the current day.  Or, if max daily caffeine level could be tracked in addition to total caffeine intake. Three cups of coffee drank before 8 am has a different effect than three cups spread through the day,  thought the total amount of caffeine intake is the same.
Design could be better, but as a tool it gets the job done.

I've been looking for an app similar to this but tracks the amount of medicine in your blood stream. I can't find a single app that does this, any chance you could make one? I tried to edit this one but without being able to change the half life it's impossible.

It wouldn't win a beauty contest but this app does exactly what I wanted it to. At first I wanted to keep my caffeine levels within certain limits during work hours to boost performance but the truly valuable insight has been that my sleep is really affected if I try to sleep above a certain threshold. Now I am able to see whether a drink I'm thinking of having now is going to keep me awake several hours later or if I'm safe to go ahead. I've also learned how and when I begin to become caffeine dependent.

I had problems viewing all the functions on my Galaxy S4 as it didn't show the 3 dot menu button at the top of the screen like the screen shots seen on here. Contacted the developer who helped me solve the issue. You need to use the phone's menu button at the bottom. Now I can start getting a better estimate of my caffeine intake as I can customise the type of coffee I drink.
replyContent: You can access the overflow menu options on your Galaxy S4 using the back lit menu button to the left of your hardware button below the screen.  Thanks for purchasing!

content: Changed the way I looked at caffeine, some. Wish it used BMI instead of weight/gender to calculate. Maybe more variables could be introduced over time?
Looks useful but all of the drinks I drink aren't listed and I can't find the amount of caffeine they have to manually enter them
replyContent: Checkout http://www.caffeineinformer.com/ for a large database of drink caffeine information.  If you still would like a refund, send an email to rogan.software@gmail.com.

content: Simple app to estimate caffeine metabolization, made a substantive difference in my caffeine consumption.

Great tool to visualize your caffiene level in order to reduce dependence on caffiene. I could tell how much made me feel bad and what my lower threshold was as well. After a week or so, I was able to start reducing the amount I needed by keeping my level out of the high and low threshold. I'd like to see the interface reworked and a good representation of the ideal zone you define for your caffiene level.
Track caffeine levels.
Very Helpful
Decent. Could be better.
replyContent: Let me know how!

content: A good way to track caffeine. It would be good if we could search a database for actual barcodes or products for their specific caffeine amounts, for more accurate tracking.
The refresh button causes the mg of caffeine to go haywire.  Needs a quick update.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback.  If you could export your data to CSV and email to rogan.software@gmail.com that would help me troubleshoot the problem.

content: Pretty good

Works great, tracks perfectly and the graph and notifications are very good features. Of course the common complaint is how basic this app looks and my other complaint is that the graph range on the x axis is too long. The time needs to be stretched out more. Perhaps the graph could scroll. Other than that it would be good to know when to have a cup of coffee to maintain a certain caffeine level and a notification when to do so. If these features are ever added I will change my rating.
I use this so I do not have too much caffeine when I go to bed.

I think it's obvious that it needs a real design, but that aside I would love some more data. I see the charts and graphs, and current caffeine level but I would like to know when I add a drink what the impact will be on my day (16oz coffee +180mg caffeine, or whatever it is) instead of waiting 45 minutes to see the total number..   Also the daily graph is handy but with no real ability to get the exact total of each day its useless. If i was trying to track my caffeine intake for any purpose more than a curiosity I would need these numbers.

Decent and useful app but leaves alot to be asked for. On all aspects I'm wishing there was more details, more functionality. It's the only app with its function on android so worth paying a buck for, but if there was competition I'd say this belongs in the free app category due to its bleakness. Has potential to be really good though if future releases add much more features,  better user interface
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback.  Feel free to share desired features.

content: No feature creep.  Well done.

I use the app most days and it is quiet good in letting you know how much caffeine you have in your system.  There are not many drinks in the list, but you can look up values and add your own. There are no options to add in food items, you have to add them as drinks and add their caffeine amounts in. Its OK and cheap enough. Its been educational for me to realise when I am ODing on caffeine what the effects are and to avoid that by checking my values before taking on more caffeine.

Needs a real designed UI, more functional graphing and deeper stats, options for notifications, more preset drinks and a setting for sleep time projection (under 100 mg for example). Otherwise it's pretty OK and does its job.

I'd like to suggest the following changes:  1. The date and time the caffeine (coffee) is consumed seems to be wrong. It does not seem to be the local time where I am. I may misunderstand how to use the app though but that's how it looks to me, even after I double check the date when I am inputting the data.  2. I realise you explain the colour coding system on the play website. But it would be great for new users to have that in the app when they first use it.  3. There should also be a way of deleting input which may be mistakes, tests or simply inaccurate. For example, I often put test data into an app to see if it works and does what it says and I like/understand the input/output(graphs, charts - whatever). However, I cannot delete  my test entry I made after I installed the app so now all subsequent readings are influenced by that fictitious test cup of coffee.  I've rated the app 4/5 and will hapily edit the rating if/when these are implemented. Good app though.
Perfect for keeping your caffeine level steady. No headache no jitters. A caffeine junkie's dream!
Need to let us show time caffeine taken as an option instead of how long ago. Also could use interface improvements
Does exactly as you'd expect.  However, it would be nice to be able to view farther back into the projection chart history.
Just what I was looking for, but there is definitely room for improvement.

I am left disappointed with this app because there are a number of features that are broken or missing. You need to add an option for am/pm instead of 24hr for time entry. I should be allowed to enter in a drink at a future time, say if I'm going to drink 1 hr from now and I wanted to compare the effects of a coffee vs a soda.   There is also no option to indicate rate of drinking. Whether I chug my coffee or sip it over an hour, the app has no way of distinguishing. Thus the graph will always look the same - a cycle of spiking and decaying.   Graph: The numbers on the X and Y axes are so small that you have to squint to read them. You must add the ability to zoom in/out if nothing else.   The notifications need to be overhauled. There should be more granular options, say If I want to be notified ONLY when I go below the minimum threshold. Right now it's just "all notifications on" vs "all notifications off" which isn't very helpful.  Not a bad start but I really hope you take this feedback seriously and integrate it in future updates.

Pretty great, but I wish it included things other than drinks, it's silly to have to add things by ounce. I'd much rather prefer if you could just add the mg caffeine you consume at a time. The graphs are cool but it's really hard to read them. Wish I could own and zoom.
Please add more options for the graphs
replyContent: Looking into updating the graphs.  Thanks for the feedback.

content: Overall,  a useful app.  The graph is extremely difficult to read.  Blue text on black background is bad.  Graph should allow zooming in as well as scrolling left to right. Drink input is instantaneous but you don't drink a large coffee in one minute.  How about giving a length of time that a drink took to drink? How about personal profiles for more than 1 drinker? Do all brands of coffee have the same caffeine level?  A database with different brands of coffee would be good.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback.  Appreciated.

content: Few tweaks needed, ability to edit drinks. Cheers from reddit! Edit: Just received the notifications about approaching a limit. Awesome
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback!

content: Dev is responsive too.  Just want a way to adjust half times or add other medications but works amazingly well to keep you in the zone.
Horrible app. Most of the screens will not show.. Big waste of my money...
replyContent: Sorry to hear you are having problems with the app, Michelle.  If you can provide more detail on your troubles, I'd be happy to help resolve.  If I cannot fix your problem - be happy to refund.

content: Great way to track my caffeine intake!

Overall a rather intuitive app to use. Although I am biased toward dark themes, whereas this app's theme is quite white, I found the UI to be quite pleasant and functional. The graph plotting is really cool.  There are a few features I'd like to see added/modified. First, it would be cool if it could add a future time for a drink, so it could help predict the effects of future consumption. Also I'd like to see the level history and projection graph have a customizable time window, instead of just one day forward and back.  Overall, nice app. Keep up the good job!
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback!

content: Good app. Would be 5 stars if their was an option to use the metric system.
replyContent: Latest version now has option to set both drink size units and body weight to metric units.  Please update rating to 5 stars! :)

content: The the new light theme wastes my phone's battery, and I think you must have moved the controls around, because I can no longer enter my coffees as quickly as I used to before the latest update. Used to love this app, but...
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback.  Sorry you are not liking everything about the changes.  The "add drink" button has been added back prominently to main screen in latest update.

content: As others have said, it does what it does well, but it needs more features. I would like to be able to add custom substances (i.e., not just caffeine) with a custom half life (or choose from presets, like alcohol, THC, prescriptions, etc) and track those as well.
For 5 stars,  I'd like to see metric system for body mass,  and a zoomable graph.
replyContent: Latest version now has option for metric system body weight.  Thanks for feedback!  Feel free to update rating :)

content: Helps to keep caffeine level optimum when working and before going to sleep. A widget would be more than welcome however, since it would be much more convenient to see the current caffeine level straight from the home screen.

Great idea for an app, only problem I've found is in reading the level that you'll be at at a certain time, because the scale down the bottom is so small and increases in 4 hour increments. 5 stars if you added vertical gridlines on the chart. Cheers.
I have turned them off but still they occur..

This isn't what I was hoping for. I really wanted an Android version of Caffeine Zone, but this is a poor substitute.  The graph doesn't show your max and min levels, like I had hoped.  Graphically, it's awful too. Quite disappointed really.
Graph doesn't show upper or lower levels, making it fairly pointless.
Reviewers who give poor marks for lack of menu items haven't bothered to read very good instructions on adding your own.

The charts are a great upgrade from the Lite version. It's nice to see what my projected caffeine level is now, and what it would be later if I drank something now.   Would be nice if it could import the data from the Lite version, though. The tracking stuff doesn't have much use for a day or so without it.

...you need to find out yourself the information about caffeine eg. what's the optimal level before unwanted side effects.  Graphs could have default/customizable information lines that you could activate, like "get your caffeine level this low before 22:00" or "Shake hands time!" or "Blood pressure high enough for you?". Not as an encouragement but so that you could try to avoid those caffeine levels.  Finnish cup of coffee has about 0,9mg/ml so I tried to edit the standard Coffee -drink from the drink menu. I found out that there's no editing option so I had to just make new one and delete the old one.  Also have you considered the fact that caffeine probably takes also time to get in to your system? You could think adding an little side option for "condensation" notifications. It would be cool if my phone reminded me to drink more water, not just less coffee. :D   You have and great app going on here, I hope you have the time to develop it more inviting and user friendly!
Super fast response from developer, and app does what's on the label.
needs the ability to delete past entries. needs to show bands of target levels... High medium low. Just the graph by itself isn't so useful.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback.  You can delete past entries by long pressing them in list to reveal context menu to edit or delete.

content: The developer is extremely-fast to respond to feedback(in my experience) and the application works very well. Great value!
Developer quickly responded to email.  Does exactly what it says.  Helps you track your intake.
A handy app for tracking the decay of caffeine in the body.  It's really useful to know when the peaks and valleys of the caffeine effect will be.

Looking over the dates of most of the comments the author doesn't appear to be overly active in adding new features. Wasn't much development throughout 2010/11  Hope to see more regular updates this year.
Does exactly what I wanted. The graph helps me plan when to stop drinking coffee to sleep.
It let's you post your caffeine intake to facebook - finally an app that does that! Lol! It's quite an interesting app though, I like it :)
There is no energy drink option or custom option to enter in another type of item w/ caffine in it. I regert spending a dollar, hopefully the next update includes more options.
I'm loving the app so far. I had an idea for a feature, and wrote the developer.  Twenty minutes later, I hear from the developer that my idea will be implemented. Great work!
I currently drink crazy amounts and wanted to cut down so i wouldn't get headaches if I didn't have a coffee in few hours rather than go cold turkey
Awesome
Fantastic! Superb App. Best caffeine tracker I've used on ANY platform. Kept my caffeine habit under control. Recommend to other coffee addicts
This app has matured well, does a lot of math behind the scenes.
